title: New Leaf Family Welcomes Attorney Katie Wilmoth to Their Team | Markets | bigspringherald.com
text:
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE
GOLDEN, Colorado, December 28, 2023— New Leaf Family is thrilled to announce the addition of attorney Katie Wilmoth to their growing team. As a skilled and compassionate family law attorney, Wilmoth brings a wealth of experience and dedication to the firm’s mission of providing exceptional legal representation in family law matters.
Christopher Anderson , CEO and founder of New Leaf Family, expressed his enthusiasm for the newest member of their team stating, “We are honored and excited to have Katie Wilmoth join the firm. She is an attorney of extraordinary talent, and caring for her clients. She will be an excellent addition to New Leaf’s team of attorneys seeking to empower our clients to make the best decisions for themselves and their families.”
With a focus on custody, child support, divorce, spousal support, property division, and modification of existing court orders, Katie has established herself as a strong advocate for her clients. She understands the unique challenges involved in cases involving children and recognizes the importance of helping parents work together for the benefit of their children even after legal proceedings have concluded. Katie firmly believes in leading by example, prioritizing professionalism, and encouraging her clients to consider the needs of their children above personal animosity towards the other parent.
Katie brings a valuable skill set to her family law practice, boasting an impressive background in business and a Bachelor of Science degree majoring in Economics from New York University – Leonard N. Stern School of Business. This background allows her to approach cases with a strategic mindset, evaluating not only the legal aspects but also the financial implications for her clients.
Rob Leitner, Chief Strategy Officer for New Leaf Family, noted that “Katie brings a wealth of knowledge and experience to the team. She is an outstanding advocate for her clients, and she continually demonstrates compassion and empathy.” Leitner added that “Katie has already made a significant impact on our legal team, and we are very excited about her future at the firm.”
Katie’s experience extends to handling high conflict cases, including those involving parental alienation, domestic violence, and alcohol and substance abuse. Her expertise in navigating complex and emotionally charged situations consistently guides her clients towards favorable outcomes, ensuring their rights and interests are protected throughout the legal process.
At New Leaf Family , the focus has always been on providing comprehensive and personalized legal services to individuals and families in need. Attorney Katie Wilmoth’s addition to the team further fortifies the firm’s commitment to excellence and strengthens their ability to serve clients facing challenging family law issues.
For more information about the legal services offered by New Leaf Family or to schedule a consultation with attorney Katie Wilmoth, please visit their website at www.newleaf.family or contact their office at (720) 712 – 3253.
New Leaf Family is a reputable law firm dedicated to providing compassionate and effective legal representation to individuals and families in and around Golden, CO. In addition to their client-centered approach, which empowers people to make decisions in their family’s best interest, New Leaf Family provides a variety of coaching and counseling services to assist clients at every stage of the process. They are committed to providing excellent legal services at fair costs as a dependable resource for local families.
The founders, Christopher T. Anderson and Penn Dodson, have been awarded Avvo 10.0 (Superb), and Martindale.com has rated the firm AV – Preeminent. Most important, however, are the clients who have experienced being a part of the New Leaf Family. See www.newleaf.family for more.

author: Samantha Money
title: WKU Player of the Week: Hilltopper baseball outfielder Ryan Wideman
text:
WKU Player of the Week: Hilltopper baseball outfielder Ryan Wideman
BOWLING GREEN, Ky. – Today’s WKU Player of the Week is Hilltopper baseball outfielder Ryan Wideman after the junior transfer had a historic week for the Tops.
Through four games, Wideman was 11-for-21 (.524) at the plate with a grand slam, five doubles, two triples and 11 RBI.
To top it off, the Georgia native recorded the first cycle in WKU program history in last week’s matchup with Southern Illinois.
So far on the season, Wideman is leading the conference in batting average (.459), hits (39), doubles (10), triples (4), RBI (26), total bases (69) and stolen bases (13).
His offensive performance also led to him being named the C-USA Hitter of the Week. It was the first time in his career to earn a weekly honor in the league.
Wideman’s efforts at the plate through those games helped the Tops continue on their winning streak as they currently stand at a 19-1 start to the season.

author: Christine Douglass-Williams
title: Iran: At Raisi’s funeral, German journalists are attacked and embarrassing moments don’t go unnoticed
text:
Iran is well known to claim that times of misfortune in the West are Allah’s punishment. How will the regime reconcile such claims with the fiasco at Ebrahim Raisi’s funeral?
Mourners attacked German journalists during Raisi’s funeral procession. The Iranian regime’s supporters have claimed that “the journalists aimed to falsely portray a low turnout at the funeral.”
“German Journalists Attacked at Iranian President’s Funeral,” Iran International , May 23, 2024:
Mourners at the funeral procession of Ebrahim Raisi in Tehran on Wednesday assaulted a news team from Germany’s television.
The German ARD news crew was targeted while filming buses that had brought pro-regime participants to the capital.
According to a foreign reporter covering the funeral, there was no apparent provocation that justified the assault by Raisi’s mourners.
“It remains unclear what narrative might have incited such anger among the attendees,” the reporter stated, highlighting the arbitrary nature of the aggression……
Meanwhile, German Chancellor Olaf Scholz sent condolences in a message addressed to Iranian Vice President Mohammad Mokhber, who is now acting president. The message said: “Our condolences go to the government of the Islamic Republic of Iran and the families of those killed in the crash.” Once again, a Western leader demonstrates no recognition of what the Iranian regime is, as well as extreme insensitivity to its victims. Such a gesture is akin to sending condolences to Nazi Germany after Hitler committed suicide.
Cheering and celebrations of the helicopter crash in which Raisi was killed continued in Iran, drawing death threats from the regime. Amid cheers over Raisi’s death, there was also mockery. An Iranian army offer who split his pants while acting as a pallbearer during the funeral didn’t escape notice:
During the live broadcast of the funeral held in Tehran for Raisi and his companions on Wednesday, an Iranian Army honor guard is seen ripping his pants while carrying the coffin of Iran’s Foreign Minister @Amirabdolahian who was killed in the Sunday helicopter crash. pic.twitter.com/jGemMOJG7l
— Iran International English (@IranIntl_En) May 22, 2024
Also, Raisi’s successor as president reportedly did his first public speech unzipped.
Amid the humiliations and despite the demise of the “Butcher of Tehran,” Iran is a brutal regime that will regroup as the contest begins among contenders for power.
Iran’s president Ebrahim Raeesi leaves a legacy of brutal repression and complicity in 1988 mass executions.
Yet Iran’s repressive machinery goes beyond the power of the president. Absent fundamental change, these violations can be expected to continue. https://t.co/JdpqykEViR pic.twitter.com/F3POr7xlIO
— Human Rights Watch (@hrw) May 21, 2024
One of the well-recognized contenders for the presidency is former president Mahmoud Ahmadinejad. His “former exorcist” has stated that Ahmadinejad “regularly holds secret meetings with his new team in preparation for the 2025 presidential election, and intends to make a comeback.”

author: Terry Ramos
title: Do You Have What It Takes to Be a Great Bodybuilder?
text:
Excelling in bodybuilding requires mental fortitude and discipline, above all. Bodybuilding is a proper art form that requires time, dedication, and consistency to excel. It’s not merely about spending hours in the gym lifting weights. Aspiring bodybuilders should focus on continuous improvement and refinement, never believing they can stop or rest on their laurels. Even when they reach their physical goals, the journey of self-improvement must persist to stay ahead of the competition.
There are numerous perspectives on what defines a great bodybuilder. However, this article will emphasize widely accepted principles, showcasing essential qualities and guidance on this journey. Let’s delve into what it truly means to be an exceptional bodybuilder.
Overview — Who Is a Bodybuilder?
A bodybuilder is an athlete who uses weights for resistance and strength training to build and improve the body’s muscularity. The goal is to be aesthetically pleasing with lots of muscle, low body fat , and a strong X-frame ( broad shoulders and lats and a smaller waist ). Of course, the art of bodybuilding isn’t particular to men; women can be bodybuilders, too. Being a bodybuilder means adopting the lifestyle of regularly hitting weights and competing at high levels.
So, if you’re thinking of becoming a bodybuilder, it’s important to note that it isn’t just a process, but a lifelong journey that never stops. It takes sacrifice, patience, determination, will, consistency, a strict meal plan, and ample time in the gym.
So, How Can You Become a Bodybuilder? Building a bodybuilder’s physique worthy of the stage will take years. However, beginners will see motivating results after a few weeks. Studies show muscle thickness changes after eight weeks with constant resistance training (1) . Below is a list of valuable tips for becoming a bodybuilder.
Education Committing to the lifestyle of bodybuilding requires a lot of studies and research. This helps you get a base knowledge of what you’re getting yourself into. Looking out for gyms in the area or talking to a professional bodybuilder or coach helps, too. When researching, it’s essential to note the equipment , types of strength training exercises, and how they could help your bodybuilding goals.
Strength training exercises include:
Free Weight Exercises : These consist of dumbbells , barbells , and kettlebells . Stationary Machines : These are major machines (plate-loaded and cable machines) like leg presses , leg extensions , leg curls , and shoulder and chest presses, which can be used to build multiple muscle groups. Resistance Bands : Elastic bands that improve overall fitness and build muscle and strength (2) . Bodyweight Exercises (Calisthenics): These exercises require using your bodyweight to build strength and muscle. Some examples are push-ups , sit-ups , burpees , squats , lunges , planks , and crunches . Do comprehensive research on these types of exercises and the target muscles. You can do a lot of strength training research to help you better understand the training that suits your body’s needs and prepares you for your bodybuilding journey.
Plan a Follow Through Fitness Routine It’s important to map out a fitness plan to achieve your bodybuilding goals. It helps you track your progress and makes addressing any necessary changes easier. A good fitness routine enables you to target all muscle groups, not leaving anyone behind. Committing to a good fitness routine will allow you to progressively overload , which is crucial for muscle growth and strength.
A fitness routine could contain different exercises that adopt distinct movements. It can be an isolation exercise , which means using a single joint, or a compound exercise , which recruits more than one joint and targets multiple muscle groups.
You can also try different training splits that are effective and guarantee to hit multiple muscle groups over a period. Here is a list of some training splits you can try below:
Bro Split: This training split allows you to train one or two muscle groups weekly. Push-Pull-Legs Split : Regarded as one of the best training splits. This training split hits every muscle group by grouping each part of your body into push, pull, and leg exercises . Five-Day Split: You train multiple muscle groups over five days weekly. Upper-Lower Split: This splits your upper body training into the upper and lower body . Nutrition & Dieting
We must emphasize the importance of nutrition in bodybuilding. Apart from lifting weights for muscle growth, what you eat equally affects how your muscles develop. A good meal plan will help your muscle and strength development (3) .
Now that we understand that eating right is suitable for your bodybuilding goals , what are the right foods to eat so we can build muscles? The simple answer is eating the right macronutrients, including protein, carbohydrates , and fats . Protein helps build muscle quickly, and having at least one gram of protein daily is necessary. You can find proteins in white eggs , meat , fish , and beans.
Complex carbohydrates are the primary energy sources your body cells and organs need to perform functions. This can also help with the necessary energy for your exercises. You can find carbs in oatmeal, bread, brown rice, sweet potatoes, and whole grains. Healthy fats help our body absorb the essential vitamins our bodies need. Fats also help boost your testosterone , which is vital in bodybuilding.
Tracking your calories is also important to keep your body in check. To lose weight and gain muscle definition, go into a calorie deficit and do the opposite, a caloric surplus , to gain mass. Ensure that you eat mainly whole foods throughout the process for best results.
What It Takes to Be a Great Bodybuilder Being a great bodybuilder means consistency in training around the clock. Bodybuilders focus on different aspects of their training during various periods, such as the off-season or in-season.
Training During the Off-Season The off-season is a period during the calendar year when bodybuilders focus on growth areas. This period usually lasts three to six months, depending on the training goal. During this period, you also add a lot of lean muscle and focus on building strength.
Competition Preparation & Training Competition prep depends on the type of bodybuilder preparing for a major competition, but it’s usually, on average, eight to ten weeks out. During this phase, you try to cut as much fat as possible and focus on building muscle and definition. You also stick to your training split and try to avoid getting any injuries leading to the competition. The key is to train hard, train smart, eat right, and work on your poses .
Recovery Training hard is essential to be the best, but it’s also important to rest. Tasking your muscles can be detrimental if you don’t get adequate rest during the off-season or on-season. Know when to deload and take breaks from the gym, and focus on active recovery. Efficient recovery will allow you to train harder and respond to training more positively.
